[STEP 21] Fixed CORS blocking POST to /api/posts (2026-07-19):
           ROOT CAUSE: Custom CorsMiddleware was prepended alongside Laravel 13's built-in HandleCors,
           causing a dual-middleware conflict. Additionally, the server was never restarted after changes.
           The built-in HandleCors (backed by fruitcake/php-cors) was already in the default global
           middleware stack — the custom one was redundant and conflicting.
           
           Changes made:
           - Removed \App\Http\Middleware\CorsMiddleware::class prepend from bootstrap/app.php
           - Deleted app/Http/Middleware/CorsMiddleware.php (no longer needed)
           - Cleared all Laravel caches (config, cache, route)
           - Killed and restarted php artisan serve on port 8000
           - Verified CORS headers present on both OPTIONS preflight and POST responses
           
           The built-in HandleCors reads config/cors.php automatically:
           - paths: ['api/*'] matches all API routes
           - allowed_origins: [env('FRONTEND_URL', 'http://localhost:5173')]
           - supports_credentials: true

